<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98821250579266></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98821250579266><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98821250579266>RE: Halfing is the best race for a cleric.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=98821250579266#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=35078><span id=Scholar>Gestalt</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>119 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 11:28 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hide and sneak are fine, so long as people understand that no class other than rogue can combine hide/sneak at same time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Many don't seem to understand that and it could confuse people that don't.<br><br>Also, low charisma has no effect on fear.  And neither does high charisma either.  Necros with horrible cha and enchanters with 200ish cha using the same fear spell and both same level, will both fear the same.  Sure, you could get a string of resists or short fears as either of them.  But that's chance.  Fear kiting with either is great, really only determining factor is level deifference, MR of mob, and what fear spell is being used (higher ones generally work better, or least they SHOULD, hehe).  So the cha of cleric means nothing for fearing...  What it will mean is he'll need a lot more cha boosting items or have someone cha buff him with a spell so he can buy his all important gems for hp buffs.<br><br>BTW, I have a DE cleric, and his cha sucks at 60 (i think).  Gotta get him buncha plus charisma items so he doesn't go into the poor house buying gems and spells in later levels.<br>&nbsp;<br>Gestalt<br>60 Grandmaster<br>ARo</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
